          <h2 id="roadmap" class="govuk-heading-m">What we are working on</h2>
          <p class="govuk-body">We are planning a range of new features to give users greater flexibility in the forms they design.
            <table style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: left; border:1px solid #dee0e2;" border="1">
              <tr>
                <th>Done</th>
                <th>In progress</th>
                <th>Coming up</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>You can now use MoJ Forms to:
                  <ul>
                    <li>create, test and publish forms using a variety of question formats</li>
                    <li>guide users through complex journeys using branching</li>
                    <li>check user answers with custom validation rules</li>
                    <li>generate reference numbers and take payments through GOV.UK Pay</li>
                    <li>collect user data by email in PDF and CSV formats</li>
                    <li>send users a confirmation email when they submit their answers</li>
                    <li>monitor performance with Google Analytics</li>                    
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td>We are currently working on:
                  <ul>
                    <li>allowing users to edit their form name and URL</li>
                    <li>introducing a process for performing final checks on new forms before they go live</li>
                    <li>improving the accessibility of the editor</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td>We are exploring how to:
                  <ul>
                    <li>integrate forms with other services using an API</li>  
                    <li>allow multiple users to work on the same form</li>
                    <li>enable form owners to unpublish and delete forms</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
              </tr>
            </table>
          </p>
